caption: Nice place to drink some wine and share with friends
Wow, wow, wow.  Amazing food and service!

The food here is SO amazing. It is a small menu (unless you come on Saturday when the crepes are around), but all of it is delicious. Saturday brunch is personally my favorite.  Beyond the food, they go above & beyond with service. Also, if you have to wait it might be tempting to get coffee elsewhere... but if you can resist, they have great coffee here too.

Good food and friendly service... But they had the music way too loud! Thankfully my server understood how hard it was to talk and they did turn the music down. They have a good list of specials on the white board in addition to their menu.

Lovely little restaurant that is always busy on the weekends. Finally got to try it and it did not disappoint! Food took some time to come, but it was totally worth the wait. Would definitely recommend trying out as one of the Gainesville downtown musts.

Unfortunately , for the first time in Gainesville we were discriminated against   tonight because of either our color or ethnic background. As usual tried to support a local gainesville restaurant . But for the first time it happened to go to this restaurant in a group from the same cultural background. we were ignored  while waiting to be seated like anyone else , the hostess was bypassing us and not once asked  us how many is our party , or name or if we prefer to sit inside or outside. after 40 minutes and everyone else came after us got seated and only because we complained , the manager tried to make things better but after telling us that we were intimidating! the hostess until we left she had not apologized.  we left without eating because it started raining outside and they could not accommodate us inside. they pretended to be polite  but would not give us an explanation why we were ignored over and over again although you can not miss us in the small space! I heard that they might be picky  and discriminatory with their customers , but as a man who believes and works in science I could not believe it without evidence. Sad day for the community.

My partner and I had dinner from here today. Let me just say, we’ve been to France, we’ve eaten at French restaurants in big cities and Alpin Bistro delivers in all regards! Super fresh produce, great execution in their dishes. Had the quiche of the day that was perfectly cooked and super flavorful and a croque madame that was expertly prepared and the egg was excellent technique. The service was great too! Definitely going to keep supporting this great spot!
Excellent food and service.
The best food in Gainesville. Period!
The only reason why we didn't give a 5 is because of the limited menu. It made it more challenging to find exactly what we were in the mood for. What we did order was impeccable. Highly recommend.
Great place to have lunch! Enjoyed a stuffed tomato and rice salad! Beautiful glass of rose! Lovely!
The food is really good. Covid prep is really being given a lot of effort. Definitely give it a go.
Incredible...the best food in Gainesville!! Try them ASAP. The Lardon is excellent, and every quiche is unique and special. But everything on the menu is fantastic.
Tapas And Affaghato an amazing yummy dish. A lot of vegetarian options also. Superb Ambience
Go now! Everything we tried was fantastic. The escargot, quiche and wine were all paired perfectly.
decent food and environment is great
I loved the atmosphere and the food was great, I highly recommend to check it out.

This place is pretty lit, big wine selection, lots of fancy French words. Maybe im a sus for saying this, but I would’ve liked some more English on the menus. Didn’t know what 3/4th of the menu was even saying...overall, fire as hell and I will be back for sure.
Soo nice
Nice ambiance
Even though I live in London England, I will definitely be back. Outstanding is the worse I can say.
Very interesting, charming place. Very tasty, great quality food. I loved the decent selection of rare Belgian beers - but they have much more than that ! I'll be back soon :)

The food was delicious (I had the croque - Madame)! The outdoor seating is closed off which is nice when it cold in Gainesville as it's not windy. I do not recommend sitting at the coffee tables if you are planning on getting food (you could still get the charcuterie and be comfortable) but it seems nice if you are just getting something to drink.

(Translated by Google) Small visit of a "Frenchie" on vacation, thank you for this moment, simple and tasteful meal ...  (Original) Petite visite d'un "Frenchie"  en vacances, merci pour ce moment, repas simple et de bon goût...
Way better than it was when it opened. Great quiche!

The food is unique, original, and delicious! There isn't a place like it anywhere else in Gainesville. The options are amazing. I love the cheese plates! They are so nice to munch on with friends. Plus, breakfast is a must here! They have amazing crepes. Whether you dine inside or outside the place has a lovely vibe. The staff are very considerate. I am always cold, and they offered me a blanket! They have blankets for customers! Little things like that make the place worthwhile!
Good food. An excessive amount of cheese and bread in every meal. Surprisingly their vegan platter is oddly satisfying. What's in their vegan pate? I have no idea. I don't ask. It's yummy though.

No ventilation in the kitchen, which means smoke pours into the dining room. I watched a couple stand at the entrance for 10-15 minutes before the staff acknowledged them. Food is mostly good, but some disappointments (overcooked, wet cheese; overcooked escargot). Pate was excellent, I'll give them that. Overall a really disappointing night out. I want to like this place, I just can't.
Loved it. Would absolutely come back!
The tart of the day was fantastic. I really enjoyed the creme brulee too
The ambiance is grrrereattttt but the vegan dish wasn't good( which doesn't say much about a french restaurant)

We had wonderful wine and delicious desserts in the cutest place in Gainesville. This town is desperate for great spots like this. I hope they survive unlike most everything else that comes and goes in this town.

I ate here multiple times during my visit to Gainesville because the food was that good.  I started with a hearty soup that was very nicely spiced, and a flavorful stout on tap.  The croute with mushrooms and onions was simply delicious - one of those things you keep eating even after you're full.  The quiche was light and raclette cheese gave it a nice sharpness.  Even the cappuccino was extra good. The service was uneven - I waited a pretty long time at the door one night and a long time for food the other.  But the staff all were friendly and seemed happy to be there, and the food so good, that somehow it wasn't a big deal.
Food is great, atmosphere is good when few patrons, but if there's a crowd it can be way too loud for good conversation
Just finished a brunch with family. There was a small mistake with the food but the server and chef corrected promptly. Great service and food.

Relaxing and comfortable little French bistro! I've only had the Balsamic Brie appetizer, but it was delicious, Brie perfectly melted paired beautifully with nuts, fruit, rosemary, and toasted sourdough bread. Their wine selection is also quite unique and I liked the beaulougais I tried. I'll definitely have to come back to try more food sometime. Costs are reasonable for downtown Gainesville, and the superb quality of food is worth the price. Service was attentive and fast. Decor is rustic and romantic.  Edit: Came back for date night and food was delicious!!
Loved it, great service, food and atmosphere. Would definitely go back again.

Met a friend at Alpin tonight. The service was good and the food quite tasty. There happened to be a meet up there for a group/company, which made it quite loud inside. The jazz was enjoyable, but the volume of people at the group table (with the meet up) was regrettably noticeable. We split a cheese plate, a savory tart of the day, and two desserts. All were fresh and delicious. The blue cheese was especially scrumptious. The inside is inviting and there are daily specials worth trying. If you haven't been in yet, you definitely should give it a try. For French cider, a tart with small side salad, and a chocolate mousse the bill ran around $30.

This place is amazing every time we go. I always get the omega. Cooks and staff actively support your add ins and make sure you're getting exactly what you want. Interesting ambiance very bohemian. Love it probably one of the few spots in hainedvillenfor breakfast worth going to.

Went for my first time tonight. Is actually the first French restaurant I've ever been to, what's a shocking considering most chefs are french-trained LOL. Anyway, I want to start by saying the service was Tip-Top all the way around--very awesome. I tried several different dishes and everything was fantastic! The only downside it seems (to me only!) in French cuisine is that everything is really heavy and all kinds of a fantastic cheeses. Unfortunately, I have a bit of a dairy allergy, so this is not a place I'll be with a frequent often, but if I didn't, I would be there all the time! I give them five stars because it's not their fault that cheese makes me feel crummy. Anyone who loves cheese and fine food with outstanding service will absolutely enjoy Alpin.
Food and atmosphere were great!
Always amazing food and service.
Cozy atmosphere with tastey offerings.  Nice patio space out back.
Good portions and great atmosphere
Great environment and the staff very attentive.. Appetizers are in good portion and prices are reasonable.. Go when the sun is setting.. It makes for nice lighting
Great Brunch

Classic french bistro food. Loved everything, from the soup du jour, tarte du jour, sandwiches, and desserts. I thought the creme brulee was especially wonderful. Nice atmosphere, wished they were open for lunch during weekdays.
Amazing food. Amazing service. Totally worthwhile
Wonderful atmosphere, food, and service!!
Overpriced..."french" restaurant. A weird layered bread dish with sliced ham lunch meat in it and baked..Never going back.

Disappointed that it was basically just open faced sandwiches with no other French cuisine. Was really excited to see a "French bistro" open and then quickly let down by the menu as they basically decided to focus on just one type of French food... and that type of food is particularly boring and doesn't scream "french". The sandwiches are good, but they are very heavy- so be prepared for that. I feel like they did what they are trying to do well and if they update their menu in time it could be a much better restaurant.

Horrible, horrible, rude service. Food ok. Opened at 11. We got there at 11:05 with 11:15 reservations. Waited 30 minutes for coffee. Overall took 2 hours for a very simple breakfast. NO apology, just excuses over and over that they were short staffed. No manager to speak with.
We came for dinner, drinks and charcuterie. Had a great night, food was fantastic

What an amazing gem in Gainesville. Only wish I would have found this spot sooner. Wandered into this French Bistro during our daughter's Graduation. Had some Champagne and escargots to start. Ended up cancelling our reservations at another restaurant and stayed for dinner.
Great food and very good service.

A wonderful, smaller cafe on 2nd, the Alpin Bistro is a hidden gem in Gainesville. With most downtown locations being a hugely noisy, college affair, this place stands out with a minimal and delicious menu complete with French jazz. I could eat here every night.

Went to the place because i heard it has vegan options. Turned out the options were on the regular Dinner menu and i showed up for the Saturday brunch which is a different menu that doesn't have any vegan options.  However, the staff and chef made an off-the menu special vegan crepe for me and it was great! Props to them for service. They also have a good selection of wines and i recommend the Rose.  The place is really nice, would be ideal for a date. Amazing staff and great food ( at least from a vegan point of view) and to be honest french cuisine is not known for being vegan.

Came to Gainesville for daughter's graduation. Found this gem while walking around the downtown area.  The staff was very friendly.  We started with a bottle of champagne, escargots and a leak tart.  Simply amazing.  We cancelled our dinner reservations and spent the rest of the evening at Aplin. Highly recommend.
(Translated by Google) Amazing drowned!  (Original) Amazing affogato!
Very friendly staff! Small menu, but the food is tasty, and I like the wines.
Phenomenal. Whether you come early on Saturday for crepes, or later in the evenings for dinner and cocktails, this place is amazing. Great atmosphere, great food, and great service.

This is a great date place, it is cute and has a great atmosphere. When I went there was also live music. I tasted a piece of the quiche of the day and it was delicious! the creme brulee was also very good. The only suggestion I have is to add a mixed cheese board to the menu . My order was a cheese board and, although it was really good,  I wanted a mixed cheese option, which, unfortunately was not on the menu.

Alpin is absolutely my favorite restaurant in Gainesville. I've come so many times I don't even have to look at the menu anymore. The food is super consistent and never fails to please. All the food items are made fresh, with an open kitchen which is used by most of the staff. The Classic Brie Chaud is to die for, I always want to order another! I adore the Croques, and everyone I've brought has loved them just as much.  I don't think anything is over priced, and find it strange that people think so.  The wine and beer list update frequently, and I've never had an issue finding a wine I enjoyed. Interestingly, this last time I was in I tried a few wines and my favorite was actually the cheapest! Who would've known! The service is a bit slow sometimes and they do have an issue of lack of attention, but anytime an issue arose they were quick to fix it and very accommodating. (I assume they just know how good they are !!) I work at a bar in town and I always recommend Alpin, and many of my guests come back thanking me! I'm moving out of Gainesville soon but I will definitely be coming back to Alpin as many times as possible, as I will truly miss it. Thank you for an amazing experience, every time!
It's was great! Delicious sandwiches!!!!
Deliciously clean and fresh food! Great atmosphere!
The cheese is so damned good, you'll be thinking of it until you come back for more! Camembert is so delicious and perfectly melty. Cute atmosphere, it's great for date night!
The food was great loved the ambiance. Was a little noisy
Amazing food and great atmosphere

Every time I come here I leave feeling great. I eat great food that was carefully prepared and thought went in to each dish it seems. The side salad with the entrees had slightly pickled vegetables which brought a brightness to the lettuces. The cheese selections have never been a bad decision and the creme brulee is always great. Brunch is amazing because of the crepes. Recommend this place for a great date night.
I love this place.  I've never had a bad thing on their menu.  Their staff is wonderful and I go back all the time.

Alpin is one of my top 3 restaurants in Gainesville! I love everything about it. The atmosphere, the wine, the food - especially the food, I try something new every time and I've never had something I didn't enjoy. They have menu items that change seasonally, as well as day-to-day, and it's all wonderful. Brunch might have to be my favorite thing, though, as few things compare to eating a savory crepe and sipping on some Paris tea from Harney & Sons tea company.
Literally the best place I’ve ever had pizza at. The service was amazing and fast they treated me so nice. 10/10 recommend for all pizza lovers

This is a great place for an evening drink and food with friends. They have nice lighting and it has a romantic atmosphere. The cheese plates are great for sharing, but they don't give you enough bread, and they charge you for extra.  The monsieur and quiche dinners are very tasty, but the serving sizes can be small if you're really hungry. I think it's overpriced for what you get. But I keep coming back, because I always enjoy the music, the nice service, and the environment it all creates.

This is my third time trying out Alpin and this restaurant never fails to be better every time I visit!  My big and I went for dinner around 7PM on a Thursday night and it wasn't too busy! But when we left around 9PM, it was packed. Tip: go earlier! We were seated immediately and was given the special of the day which we pretty much order from, haha. There dishes are so unique and delicious.  We started off with the leek soup - creamy and subtle! The taboulé, merguez, zaalouk with house roasted bell pepper hot sauce had the perfect combination. The zaalouk eggplant dish was roasted with the bell pepper which it was filled with exotic flavors. The zaalouk mixed so well with the taboulé rice! I do have to say the merguez which was the lamb sausage was bland and lacking something to it. But, I think that was the purpose of the dish since everything else in that dish was flavor-filled. My favorite entree was the bacon and potato quiche! It was such a large portion and you honestly can't go wrong with this dish. Lastly, we order the special of the day, lemon and basil creme brulee. I cannot stress how yummy this dessert was! It's an interesting combination but yet, so good. Best part was the caramelized sugar on top!  Attentive service, unique and appetizing dishes, and warming/comfortable environment! I highly recommend checking out Alpin with your friends or family!

A lovely Bistro for a glass of wine and a nice cheese board. It has sandwiches, tartines and quiches, and those are good for a quick snack but this is not a fancy restaurant. Excellent for what it is!

One of the nicest & best kept secrets in downtown Gainesville. Great specialized food from the French cuisines. Authentic with nice atmosphere. Ask for the guitar live shows, they're nice. Great choice for an evening outing on town. Would go many times when given a chance. It's a bit on the smaller size, cozy but may get crowded, reserve ahead.
Kind of expensive but the food tastes good.

I was a little confused when I heard that a French restaurant was opening up in the space where Spankk night club used to be, but I'm SO glad I checked this place out. The food, guys, the food is incredible. I love French cuisine and this place nails it. Everything was tasty and fresh. The service we received was excellent too. Our server warned me that the quiche would take a while to bake. I understood and told him I was happy to wait. While I was waiting he brought over some bread and goat cheese for my boyfriend and I free of charge because the food was talking longer than usual. That kind of service is bringing me back here. You have to check this place out if you care about local dining in Gainesville.
(Translated by Google) Very good, worth it  (Original) Muito bom, vale a pena

Food was very good. Had the salad special and a cheese plate.  Super generous portions and great flavor.  Wines and french cider were well curated.  Service was nice,  but pretty slow, and the restaurant wasn't all that busy.  I would definitely come back. Pleasent atmosphere.
Always a great experience dining and drinking here

A quaint hole in the wall that serves authentic French plates and other small tapas. It's an amazing date spot or even just a place to grab a glass of wine and hang out. The food is absolutely delicious and worth every penny. I highly recommend any of the quiches on special or the croques on menu.

I have spent Valentine's day with my girlfriend at this location 2 years in a row. The vibe is fancy while also casual. Their website design is astounding, kudos! I recommend this location for a date night for any couples in the area. A great place for wine and cheese.
We got the vegan charcuterie trio. 10/10
Love it. Awesome service, awesome food.

Delightful and cozy bistro great for sharing wine, time, and cheese with a while group of friends, or just someone special. The atmosphere is nice, but the live music can get a little loud sometimes. The staff are also capable of suggesting good pairings, vital for a small place like this. The small plates are excellent, and having tried most on the menu, come highly recommended. The location is alright, and if you come after 6, there is parking easily available. Otherwise, you've got to pay for parking or find street parking nearby.

This is my new favorite place in Gainesville.  The atmosphere is relaxing, the food is amazing, and the wine selection is fantastic.  It’s the perfect place to unwind with friends or just to enjoy spending time with your favorite person.  Truly a treasure.
Food is great here
Good food and friendly people
Nice place. Would recommend their lemon tart.
Cozy atmosphere and wonderful aromas. There's a lovely outdoor area as well
Beautiful place with good food. Their menu has more selections now than in 2016. Just be prepared to spend at least $12 per item.
Delicious food and wonderful service!
Yummy mixed drinks, amazing atmosphere, friendly staff. Always recommend !
The food is beautiful and everyone there is so friendly. Really enjoyed Saturday brunch.
Great food and atmosphere.
Cozy place. Great food. Nice small outdoor courtyard. Creme brulee!

If you're looking for real French cuisine, I would not suggest this to anyone who knows a true French cuisine and experience. The escargot was prepared on a "snail dish" with the garlic butter and fresh herbs inaccessible due to the dish not having holes large enough to dip or soak them in. The croque monsieur was overloaded in cheese. The water is kept in glass bottles without a cap or any sort of cover for who knows how long as it is lukewarm to the taste. There are no more "carafe d'eau" besides the one on the table that's sitting there when seated and when you ask for a French baguette....they don't even have it made fresh. Claims to be a legit French restaurant that resembles very little of that of a French Restaurant.  Perhaps I have high expectations given I was very excited to have run across something that reminded me of my childhood, but I was quite saddened due to the lack of many things. I was hoping the staff said things with a French accent too, but then again, things here are Americanized.  I expected more of a selection too. I could hardly find anything at all to eat on the menu. I found it to be well overpriced for the quality of food.
Food and service are amazing. Love the atmosphere, the craft involved, and attention to every detail.
Such a gem! Alpin has a well-curated beer and wine list (no liquor), a delicious bistro menu, and a lovely atmosphere. Regular live music and seasonal specials keep it interesting.
Excellent service and superior quality food.  Gourmet dining experience. At first I thought it was pricey for the product but the flavors of the food was appropriate for the money.
Amazing service wonderful food and great atmosphere for our first time it won't be our last absolutely loved everything
Excellent, can't wait to go there again.

An amazing, amazing experience nestled in a little nook of Gainesville. Everything was delicious, down to the complimentary side salad! Highly recommend trying both the beer and desert menu- the mousse is to die for! Vegan options push this over the top to make it a truely "Gainesville" restaurant.
Trendy authentic French bistro in downtown Gainesville...owners are very nice! Great food/drink options and tons of legit French wines!
The rustic side of French cuisine in the heart of Gainesville. Rich, delicious, unpretentious.
Amazing food, great drinks and better service. A jewel in G-Ville
Love this place!  So clean and classy :)

Super disappointed by this place. I am French and speak it, and this food is very much just American cuisine. The crêpes were not good and seemed very overpriced for such, and I was not a fan of the mimosas my husband and I ordered. Also, when we went they were out of ingredients for two of the five sweet crêpes they offer. I didn’t even get to try what I wanted and what I received was not good. Similarly, I was not impressed by the staff. They weren’t very friendly and we were sat at a table with two other couples, both of whom didn’t want anyone by them and tried to move to a new table. It was very smoky as well, just because it’s a small space, so just be prepared for that.
Great food, service and wine

Love going to Alpin. It's an amazing, quant spot in downtown that always has a great selection of wine and amazing food. It's run by a couple that moved here from Europe and it has a neat European style restaurant feel. I've never had a bad dish or a bad wine here. They really do it right. Amazing date night place!
Well- crafted sparkling wine cocktail and fantastic atmosphere!
Very classy atmosphere and delicious food and wine
Amazing food, absolutely delectable!

For a moment you forget you're in Gainesville Florida, you feel like in the middle of France or the French Alps. The food is phenomenal, the drinks great, not too pricey, and staff very friendly! If you want something different I recommend this place.
This place never disappoints. Just had an amazing and very filling antipasto plate with a fat glass of wine. I always leave this place full and happy even if I just order one dish.
Amazing food and a great wine selection in a comfortable and authentic atmosphere.
Trendy atmosphere, great wine selection, never too crowded.
Great wine and fantastic small bites to go along. All hand made with care and great atmosphere.

The cheeses here were absolutely amazing. The blueberry lemon tart was the special of the day and tasted fantastic. I would recommend going here if you are in a wine and cheese mood because you can't go wrong with the selections
Stopped by this place after dinner to share a bottle of wine and some dessert with friends. Atmosphere, service, wine and crepe brûlée were all fantastic. I plan to visit again

Went for a friend's late night bday dinner.  Nice atmosphere.  Friendly staff.  Good service.  Food was good.  I'm not sure what some items were in the menu but my gf ordered something we could share.  I was a little disappointed the escargot was sold out.  Couldn't make our minds up about dessert so we ordered them all.  They all were very good.  I can't say I love this place but I def would go back and try some crepes.
Authentic French food

So darn pretty in there. And out there. We sat both inside and outside on a lovely night when they were playing live jazz. The servers are welcoming and knowledgeable. Come here for quality food and service.
My favorite place to go out in Gainesville. Their champagne cocktail is perfection.

Alpin is a French style bistro. It's a great place to come for a long (2+ hours) dinner or lunch, to sit and chat and enjoy wine, cheese and fine French food. The menu options are all on the pricey side, an the atmosphere encourages you to dress up a notch.
Brilliant food
Best food, atmosphere, and service in Gainesville.
Alpin is a gift to the Gainesville community. Great food great people and superb atmosphere. It is a rare blessing to witness someone putting this much care into serving their community and customer.
Great cheese, great beer, the charcuterie is generous and varied. This place is different in a good way. A nice relaxing date night place.
So cozy and great food.

This place was awesome. Service was a bit slower but they were slammed. Food was amazing and their wait staff were very knowledgeable and helpful. They even gave us dessert on the house without any complaint from us whatsoever! We left happy we'd found d this gem. Will definitely be back. Highly recommend!
Good place
Love this place! The food, ambiance, and service are all amazing.
Wonderful staff, beautiful atmosphere, delicious food. A welcomed cultural experience to Gainesville. When I miss Paris, this is a an easy substitute.

Highs: The signature Croques and Les Croutes are cravingly delicious. Beautiful decor and ambiance. Nice bar seating around the food prep area and outdoor courtyard if the weather is nice. Great place for conversation. Excellent live music on Wednesdays!  Low: Wine selection is mediocre and slightly overpriced.  Overall recommended! Good place for dates.
Always niche & delicious
Quality food, quality wine and quality staff. Vegetarian options every night and often you will find vegan soups and salads. Alpin is a charm and a great addition to Gainesville.
Perfect place for date night!

It's exactly what it says, a French cafe. Simple food of the highest quality. The patio is intimate and welcoming. A great place for a casual dinner with friends or a special person. The staff is friendly and service is excellent. If you can save room for desert.
Great food and love their Pink Cocktail.

I love this place. The food is amazing. You can really tell the chef knows what he is doing. Every flavor melds together so well. The staff is helpful in making suggestions and I have absolutely never been disappointed in anything I've had there. From the wine to the apps to the meals everything is delicious.  The only thing that may bother some people is it is a very laid back restaurant, so just sit back and relax and don't be in a rush. Take the time to take things slowly and enjoy your time in this very-french bistro.
Love the atmosphere and food. Great to go for a late night creme brulee or warm cup of something or another. Friendly and inviting staff. Highly recommended.
Wonderful atmosphere & delightful menu, props to the team!
THE BEST AT EVERY THING

I went here with a group for a friend’s birthday.  Let me lay out some pros and cons. 1. Pro: Atmosphere.  It’s cute- we sat at a wooden bench table that was comfortable and was able to seat a large group.  The lighting is low- probably a good place for a date.  2.  Pro: Drinks.  All of us got cocktails, and we don’t care about germs, so I tried the majority of the drinks on the menu- all good!  I even took a chance with mine (it had kombucha which is quite sour, so I wasn’t too sure about a mixed drink with it) and liked it.  3.  Pro:  appetizers.  We got a couple of the cheese plates and enjoyed them. There was a Brie that had an orange spread that was good.  4.  Con. Entree.The majority of us got the special, which was a tart with tomato, mushroom, and anchovies on top.  Now, I’m aware that anchovies are salty- but this was the saltiest dish I’d ever eaten.  They left carafes of water on the table; I think I drank 5 or 6 glasses of water and I was still uncomfortably dry-mouthed because of the saltiness of the meal.  The entree was also very small- if we hadn’t gotten the appetizers I would have wanted to eat again soon- which is fine sometimes for atmosphere or particularly good food, but because I hadn’t enjoyed my entree it wasn’t a good look given the price.  The others I was with who had the same entree agreed that it was disappointing. That said, maybe it was an off night, or the chef took a chance on something that just didn’t work out, because I tried a bite of my friend’s salmon croque and that was about 1000x better.  5.  Price.  It was a special occasion so I was okay with paying more at the time, but it’s not a price I’d like to pay regularly. given my experience, I don’t think I’d take the chance on a second visit if I’m being honest.  In summary: nice atmosphere, good drinks and appetizers, maybe good for a date, but I wasn’t a fan of the entree for the price.
Very comfortable,  and tasty.
Very good food,  pleasant staff and atmosphere
The Brie De Normandie Chaud is amazing. Must try. Service can be much better
Crepes were scrumptious.
Great food and wine, and an excellent atmosphere for enjoying the company of friends.
The food is great and the ambience is lovely

Talk about quality over everything... Alpin brings use of carefully placed fresh ingredients in a very traditional menu, one menu that's not oversaturated. Pleasant atmosphere with French ambiance with outdoor seating availability. It's like being in a romantic movie that ends only once you step out. Possibly the best brunch on Saturday here in Gainesville. Hope the dishes keep being delicious and the juices stay fresh!
Delicious
Good ambiance,  live music, great food, great wine selection! We had a great time!
Great food and drinks, staff is super as well.
Love this place. Great atmosphere, delicious food and great drinks.
Great French tapas, coffee is amazing.. vegetarian friendly too

Awesome quaint bistro. Atmosphere is really welcoming and food was great. Started with the warm Brie - extremely flavorful with the fruit topping. Then went to onion and leek quiche. Crust was perfect and quiche was nice and light and fluffy. Wonderful dishes. Couldn't complain about the cocktail or glass of wine either. Lovely place.
Amazing attentive, caring staff. Always a pleasant time and delicious refined dishes!

Great place to come for drinks after work. Just had their brunch for the first time this past weekend and highly recommend.  Crepes (savory and sweet), parfaits and quiche were all delicious. I cant remember the drinks we all had (pink panther maybe?) but its was a great way to start a Saturday. If there is space available, the cozy back porch makes for a nice retreat.
Good atmosphere, great food, large choice of good wines
The salmon croq monsieur was to die for.  Service was excellent.  French cafe music in background was a nice touch.

I really loved this place but since it is a Menu comprised of a lot of local, small batch and Specials of the Day, it changes quickly and a lot of the menu items have the same ingredients. I recommend actually walking in and having a look at the menu in case of allergies or sensitivities but if the food suits you it is SO delicious.
Solid service. Tasty food. Nice beer and wine Selection. Ask for Evan Yavelberg as he's a great server.
Delicious desserts and  friendly staff!
Seriously fantastic! Upscale experience at reasonable prices! Nice atmosphere!

Extremely authentic french cuisine, which is difficult to find anywhere. Service and atmosphere are both phenomenal but the prices are very steep for the small portions. Parking is hard to find at dinner time. Delicious brunch options also.

The menu is simple but everything delicious and perfectly paired. The savory fruit tarts with crème fraîche are insanely good. Disagree with other reviewers on time and service. Typical to the French, the ingredients are seasonal and fresh with an enjoyable atmosphere...and perhaps (European style) shared tables. This a place meant to be slowly enjoyed and food savored.

The staff was exceptional and we were treated to an absolutely beautiful spread of cheeses and vegan selections while we celebrated a friend's wedding at Alpin.  We will definitely be back the next time we are in town. Alpin is a gorgeous,  hospitable spot with a wide selection of delicious food!
Great food and friendly service. An amazing mom n pop place.
Wonderful cheese plates!!
The owners are amazing! They work hard to obtain the freshest ingredients and it shows. I really enjoyed coming here for wine and cheese 💕
Quaint little French bistro with wonderful wine selections and cheese boards.

Great people doing good things. If you want a new experience in Gainesville try Alpin. Saturday crape brunch is a must. Alpine is a date spot. a have a glass of wine a reflect spot. A place to gather with friends and share...
The best Croque Monsieur anywhere!

Very pricey for what you get. The atmosphere isn't very good. I should sit on a wooden bench or plastic chair at a picnic table for a $15 appetizer. If you like cheese or French cuisine this place might be worth a try. If you are just looking for fine dining you would be better of somewhere else. Service is pretty slow.
Crap service, horrible waits, and lousy atmosphere. Pretty sure the owner will refute my opinion rather than take the constructive criticism, however.
Amazing staff and the food was delicious. I especially loved meeting the owners of the place, they were amazing.
French accents and pastry smells and legit French beer cocktails

Great atmosphere, delicious crepes for Saturday brunch, and wine and charcuterie boards are amazing for evenings. High quality ingredients are clearly a priority and each dish is made meticulously which means everything is delicious but sometimes you may wait a while for your food. Definitely worth the wait!

Good food, slow service. Illogical reasoning for slow service. Prices are higher than reasonable, but considering the location is Gainesville you are paying for the experience of both culture and ambiance.  My husband and I went for the first time for Saturday Brunch and ordered 3 types of crepes, no drinks. Despite there being 6 or 7 staff and only five full tables seated at the time we arrived, it took almost 20 minutes to receive tap water and our table was facing the drinks station.  We then watched as people who had arrived after us received food and were finally graced with our first plate 55 minutes after ordering. While it was delicious, at this point we were annoyed as crepes are usually done in under three minutes and at no point was the restaurant full.  It took another 13 minutes to receive our 2nd plate and was then informed by our waitress that, "They can only cook 2 crepes at a time," as their reason for being slow. This doesn't make sense as we'd never received any of our three at the same time, yet other plates were flying out to the patio despite it being half empty when we arrived. The last crepe arrived 10 minutes after we finished the second and the waitress was kind enough to ask us if we wanted the bill then or after. We finished eating and paid thus closing our nearly hour and a half long brunch consisting of three delicious but pricey crepes.  We were delighted at the opportunity for French food as my husband is European and I had lived across the pond for a while, but sadly the service and wait ruined this place for us. I REALLY wanted to like this place, and the food did live up to my expectations. Sadly, the service was less concerned with our experience than joking around with each other behind the counter.  Verdict: What should have been a lovely 35 minute brunch with my husband was instead a clock-watching, stressful experience where we were made to feel unwelcome and unimportant. We likely won't return.

(Translated by Google) Love the food, the mood, the patio ... best croque-monsieur ever ... even the vegetarian one is "to roll on the ground" ... !!  (Original) Love the food, the mood, the patio... best croque-monsieur ever... even the vegetarian one is "à se rouler par terre"...!!

I had been here for a light lunch, but I recently went for Valentine's Day and had a great night. Amazing atmosphere and equally amazing food. One of a kind here in Gainesville.

Terrible dining experience here. Would give it zero stars if allowed. We went as a party of 6 on a Friday at 7:40 PM. We were seated promptly and then waited ~15minutes before a waitress came by for the first time. We ordered drinks and waters. She brought out 5 waters for 6 people of which she did not refill a single time during the entire 2.5 hour dining experience. She brought a glass of Pinot Noir when asked for Chardonnay to one of our group. With my drink order she had to come back to the table for me to remind her what I ordered. We placed our food orders and she "warned us" on Fridays it takes a while for food to come out and it will come out at different times. I guess we assumed "a while" would be more reasonable than what we experienced. After 1.5 hours we had yet to be served any food. We went to inquire about what was taking so long and then ~5-10 minutes later our food began coming out. First arrival was a ramekin of goat cheese and crostinis. It took 1.5 HOURS to bring out cold goat cheese and crostinis. Second item a few minutes after, another goat cheese plate with grapes and crostinis and pear slices. Then about 10 minutes later the baked Brie and our three orders of the Croque-style sandwiches arrived. The final item the chorizo came after we had completely eaten the rest of the food and we sent it back to kitchen. I feel pretty strongly it would have been 30 minutes longer had we not finally said something. Don't get me wrong the food was tasteful but the experience was horrible. Instead of attempting to correct the situation the manager/owner was upset at us with being upset about the service and dining experience which is a terrible approach to customer service in the food industry. We tried to discuss with her about leaving prior to the food even coming out because of how poor the experience had been but they said they will "see what they can do to make it up to us."  In the end they only took off 4 of our drinks and the chorizo plate that we sent back to the kitchen anyway from the bill. Needless to say I will not be returning and will let everyone at UF Shands know to avoid this place. If you go, go to have a drink before going to dinner elsewhere.
Good new spot downtown, no reservations leave you at risk of a longer wait. Food was good but a bit pricey, great atmosphere, will return

Nice atmosphere and good service. Terrible music; it was literally whale noises when I was there, making it almost impossible to have a conversation. Wine with sandwiches. Nice small selection that is over priced. One odd thing was that they have single cheese plates to have with wine, not a cheese plate featuring multiple cheeses... Again overpriced IMO. Cute French server and some more friendly employees. Overall: it's okay. I'd not oppose going here again, but I won't initiate it myself.
A sophisticated, but charming mom and pop type of place. Delicious European items. I enjoyed seeing staff prepare everything to order before our eyes. Very friendly staff and owners!
We loved this restaurant. Very good and reasonably priced French wines , excellent ambiance and a delicious selection of French delicacies.
Just what Gainesville needs - the food is simple and delicious, the beer and wine fits the menu perfectly, and all the staff is friendly and helpful. Unpretentious and authentic.
Great food! Decent Beer selection and good wine.
Awesome restaurant with lots of French inspired dishes and tapas.

Stopped in during soft opening the other night. Had an amazing French red wine and my friend had a beer. Talked to the owners for a bit and they are awesome! The atmosphere is so nice here and the food seems like it will be great. I didn't have time to order food but the current offerings all sounded decadent and delicious, like something you would find at a bistro in France. Definitely worth checking out!
